reviews.text: Had dinner here once.  It’s the semi-buffet type so the choices of all-you-can-eat food were expectedly limited but tasted good enough.  Had steak as main course, it was also good but not great.  Pretty nice atmosphere in the evening but I would like it lit up a bit more.  Considering it was kinda pricey, the food was not good enough to make me feel like dining here again.
Love the salad bar here. Nice restaurant for business meeting or team lunch

We had dinner for celebration, and we ordered a semi buffet there with half price for my son.

From Monday to Thursday , you can get 25% off if you order from OpenRice. Also,  you can have a free cupcake if you are on specific purpose like a birthday or anniversary.

The main course has a number of selections, including sirloin steak, bbq ribs, shrimp , and chicken. The buffet includes seafood ( oysters, crab, shrimp ), sushi,  ham, desserts, and a whole lot more. It is very good and the dessert is excellent and I like ice cream that they provide.

We enjoyed the large meal a lot and after dinner u can go to 32/f “sugar” lounge for a drink, but you need to be an adult to go there as there are “ intoxicating substances”.
You can get a perfect view up there and I really want to go again. ( Actually, we didn’t go inside because my son is not that old )

If you worry about catching the train, don’t worry as you can catch the mtr train.It opens up to around 12:30 am ( if you get drunk, I don’t know how you can go that late ) and the mtr entrance is just next to the “Feast East”.
Good food, good service. Lively place. Don't know why they put Italian in the menu to confuse people though
Breakfast costs $228 including main dish, English breakfast, and buffet. The service is quite nice. Food quality is good. You should have a try if you stay in East Hotel.

reviews.text: They may ask you to register your name and number, but the host was very friendly and helpful. The inner atmosphere is cool and spacious, lit warmly and with violet table bulbs. The outside view is superb letting you take in the harbour and downtown. Great for getting closer with friends or on a date.
Truffle chips are the thing here. Good views and has an outdoor terrace and an ok selection of beers.

Sugar has a pretty amazing view of the Hong Kong skyline and they have a tastefully decorated  interior and exterior seating. 

The drinks with the view makes the effort to get to the island if you’re in the city worth it. They’ve got a good selection of drinks. 

We were there on a weekday and we were lucky to have a seat. I’m unsure if reservations would be worth a shot during the weekends.
Might be great, but only serves guests and "members." You have to give them a bunch of info to become a member. So, y'know, nah.
This is A very nice place to hang out with friends that located at the top of the east Hong kong hotel. It has very gorgeous city and harbor view!
